{
  "stem": "18258.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His name was Zigmund, with a Z-- Z-I-G-M-U-N-D, Klamper-- K-L-A-M-P-E-R.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, OK.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You ask him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was married to my dad's older sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her name was Milly-- Emily.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I do not remember how I dealt with it then.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I remember that in fourth grade, the same school, we had a very anti-Semitic teacher in fourth grade who made remarks, and many times, disadvantaged the few Jewish boys in class.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when my dad found out about it-- I told him-- he was able to transfer me to a different school in the same district.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was very lucky to get a-- a teacher who eventually became of my favorite teachers in that year-- in that school, in that grade.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He also then prepared me for the entrance exams for the next school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- the district, as such, was average.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the street, Stumpergasse, was about 60% Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There are a lot of Jewish stores and a lot of Jewish people, and there was even one Orthodox [INAUDIBLE] house, a [? prayer ?] house, like a private little synagogue, a storefront synagogue.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember those people on Saturday mornings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We saw the-- the Orthodox Jews flock to that little-- to that little house and had their-- their services there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- we did not belong.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We belonged to a different temple-- belonged.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We occasionally went there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember the-- that particular one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the one where we went-- of course, all the synagogues at that time were Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the one I went to was in the same district in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there we occasionally, when we went, went there on the High Holidays.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
